      <methods>
         <methodStep>
            <description>
               <section>
                  <title>RDataTracker</title>
                  <para>To use RDataTracker: (1) make sure that R is installed on your computer (http://www.r-project.org/), (2) install the gtools package in R if not already installed, (3) download the RDataTracker installation file from this website to your computer, (4) install RDataTracker as an R package (e.g. use install.packages in the R console or Tools / Install Packages in RStudio), and (5) make sure that RDataTracker is loaded (e.g. via the R library command) for use in a particular session.  The RDataTracker package includes help messages for each function and user guides for RDataTracker and DDG Explorer. The user guides can also be downloaded separately from this website.</para>
               </section>
               <section>
                  <title>DDG Explorer</title>
                  <para>To use DDG Explorer: (1) make sure that the Java run-time environment (version 1.7) is installed on your computer (http://www.java.com), (2) download the DDG Explorer program from this website to your computer, and (3) double-click on the file name or icon to run it. For details on how to use DDG Explorer, see the user guide for DDG Explorer.</para>
               </section>   
               <section>
                  <title>DDG Checkpoint</title>
                  <para>To use DDG Checkpoint, download the R script (DDGCheckpoint.R) from this website to your computer and load it using the R source command. This script requires the RDataTracker library. For details, see the user guide for RDataTracker.</para>
               </section>
            </description>
         </methodStep>
      </methods>
